sub_title: Partner PwC - Consumer Markets Industry Leader PwC Nederland
summary:
I have been working at PwC since 1998. As tax partner, I have an extensive background in advising international clients on Indirect Taxes, especially in the context of large business transformation projects, ERP implementations and post-deal restructurings. I’m experienced in serving large multinational companies as a business partner, helping them to translate complex technical issues into practical implementation. 

As leader of the Dutch Consumer Markets practice, I oversee client relationships, business development and thought leadership in the Retail, Consumer Goods, and Transport & Logistics sectors. 

I am passionate about this practice because it’s all about tangible goods and services that we all use in our daily lives. These sectors are also changing rapidly as a result of, for instance, technology, e-commerce, new market entrants, changing supply chains, changing business models, and a focus on sustainability. In these interesting sector dynamics our clients are facing questions and challenges we can help them with.
